code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['rate'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', ax=ax, kde=True, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {data["rate"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month_name()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='month', y='count', data=data, ci=None, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Count')
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['series'] = data['series'].astype('category')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='series', y='count', data=data, ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count for each series?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Series')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
